{"word":"H5306 - נֹפֶךְ - nôphek - no'-fek - Emerald","slug":"H5306","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">נֹפֶךְ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>nôphek"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>no'-fek"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Emerald"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>נפך</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>nôphek</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>no'-fek</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p><ol><li>a precious stone in the high priest's breastplate<ol type='a'><li>perhaps an emerald, turquoise, ruby, or carbuncle</li></ol><li>jewels imported from Tyre</li></ol> <p />Origin: from an unused root meaning to glisten <p />TWOT entry: <a class=\"T\" href=\"S:1391 - nopek\">1391</a> <p />Part(s) of speech: Noun Masculine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4646\">H4646</a>, <a href=\"#/H4647\">H4647</a>, <a href=\"#/H5300\">H5300</a>, <a href=\"#/H5301\">H5301</a>, <a href=\"#/H5302\">H5302</a>, <a href=\"#/H5304\">H5304</a>, <a href=\"#/H5887\">H5887</a>, <a href=\"#/H8598\">H8598</a>, <a href=\"#/H8599\">H8599</a>"}]}